1286A 101st Legislative Session 1286
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1286
AMENDME NT 1286A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Overweg
1 An Act to amend the process by which moneys are distributed from the employer's
2 investment in South Dakota's future fund.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 61-5-29.1 be AMENDED:
5 61-5-29.1. There is hereby created in the state treasury a special revenue fund
6 to be known as the employer's investment in South Dakota's future fund. Moneys in the
7 fund must be used for purposes related to, to be administered by the Governor's Office of
8 Economic Development, for the purpose of making grants or awards for research and or
9 economic development for the projects in this state.
10 For purposes of this section, section 61-5-29.3, and sections 3 to 6, inclusive, of
11 this Act, "a research or economic development project" means:
12 (1) Research or equipment required in support of key industries, universities, or
13 industries determined to be viable through an economic analysis of this state, a
14 specific community, or the a research project;
15 (2) Scholarships to postsecondary educational institutions operated by the Board of
16 Regents or the South Dakota Board of Technical Education, provided that the
17 scholarships are for programs that prepare a student for a career field available in
18 this state A scholarship for any program that prepares a student for a career field
19 available in this state and is offered through:
20 (a) A public institution of higher education under the jurisdiction of the Board
21 of Regents or the South Dakota Board of Technical Education; or
22 (b) A nonpublic or tribal institution of higher education accredited by an
23 accrediting agency recognized by the United States Department of
24 Education;
25 (3) Workforce development, apprentice programs, workforce trainings, workforce
26 recruitment, or career and technical education programs offered through a:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1286A 2 1286
1 (a) A school district,;
2 (b) An accredited nonpublic secondary school, or;
3 (c) A state agency;
4 (d) A public institution subject to oversight by of higher education under the
5 jurisdiction of the Board of Regents or the South Dakota Board of Technical
6 Education; or
7 (e) A nonpublic or tribal institution of higher education accredited by an
8 accrediting agency recognized by the United States Department of
9 Education;
10 (4) The development of infrastructure required to support economic development in
11 this state;
12 (5) Projects that support business retention or expansion; and
13 (6) Recruiting out-of-state workers or projects:
14 (a) Out-of-state projects to this state; or
15 (b) Out-of-state workers to move to and work in a career field available in this
16 state.
17 Section 2. That § 61-5-29.3 be AMENDED:
18 61-5-29.3. The Governor's Office of Economic Development shall provide a written
19 report to either the Joint Committee on Appropriations or the Interim Committee on
20 Appropriations, the House Committee on State Affairs, the House Committee on
21 Commerce and Energy, the Senate Committee on State Affairs, Senate Committee on
22 Commerce and Energy, and the Government Operations and Audit Committee on a
23 biannual an annual basis the following for each award or grant made from the fund:
24 (1) The name of the recipient and the amount of the award or grant;
25 (2) The location of the recipient;
26 (3) The research or economic development purpose being funded;
27 (4) The measures being used to determine the economic impact of the award or grant;
28 and
29 (5) The number of jobs created or retained, if any;
30 (6) The balance of the fund at the time of reporting;
31 (7) The status of the research or economic development purpose; and
32 (8) For awards or grants made more than two years prior to the report, any projection
33 of jobs created or retained in this state by the recipient of the award or grant
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1286A 3 1286
1 resulting from the research or economic development purpose since the award or
2 grant was made.
3 Upon the request of the chair of a committee receiving the report, pursuant to this
4 section, the commissioner of the Governor's Office of Economic Development shall appear
5 before the committee, to answer questions that the members of the committee may have
6 on the report.
7 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 61-5:
8 If an applicant for an award from the employer's investment in South Dakota's
9 future fund is a business, the applicant must submit a business plan to the Governor's
10 Office of Economic Development before the Governor may award the applicant any
11 moneys from the fund. The applicant's business plan must include:
12 (1) The goods or services to be offered by the applicant;
13 (2) A description of:
14 (a) The types of jobs required to offer the goods or services;
15 (b) The educational requirement for each type of job; and
16 (c) The compensation package to be offered to individuals employed to perform
17 each type of job;
18 (3) The accounting practices employed by the business; and
19 (4) Other private or public funding received by the applicant.
20 Section 4. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 61-5:
21 Moneys from the employer's investment in South Dakota's future fund may be
22 awarded only to reimburse the actual cost of the research or economic development
23 project.
24 Before any moneys may be expended from the fund, the applicant shall sign an
25 agreement with the Governor's Office of Economic Development. If the award from the
26 fund exceeds one million dollars, the applicant must provide an itemized invoice of all
27 expenditures made by the applicant required in furtherance of the project and
28 documentation demonstrating proof of payment before any moneys may be expended
29 from the fund.
30 Any agreement executed pursuant to this section is open to public inspection and
31 must be posted on the state's website.
32 Section 5. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 61-5:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1286A 4 1286
1 Before the Governor may approve the award of moneys from the employer's
2 investment in South Dakota's future fund, the Governor's Office of Economic Development
3 shall provide a detailed recommendation for the award to the Governor. Upon receiving
4 approval for the award from the Governor, the commissioner of the Governor's Office of
5 Economic Development and the applicant must sign the agreement required pursuant to
6 section 4 of this Act.
7 Each agreement for an award provided pursuant to this section is open to public
8 inspection and must be posted on the state's website. Any information in the
9 recommendation agreement that constitutes trade secrets or other sensitive or privileged
10 information is not open to public inspection. Nothing in this section may be construed to
11 repeal or otherwise modify any confidentiality requirements found in state law.
12 Section 6. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 61-5:
13 The Governor's Office of Economic Development shall promulgate rules, pursuant
14 to chapter 1-26, establishing:
15 (1) The process by which an industry is determined to be a key industry for the
16 purposes of subdivision 61-5-29.1(1);
17 (2) The process by which an individual or entity applies for an award from the
18 employer's investment in South Dakota's future fund;
19 (3) The methods for assessing or estimating the economic impact, including the
20 potential investment-to-impact ratio, that a research project or economic
21 development opportunity will have on the state;
22 (4) The contractual provisions that must be included in the agreement signed by the
23 applicant and the Governor's Office of Economic Development, including:
24 (a) Performance expectations;
25 (b) A schedule for providing performance progress reports to the Governor's
26 Office of Economic Development;
27 (c) A conflict-of-interest policy; and
28 (d) Other contractual provisions that provide for the general terms and
29 conditions of the agreement;
30 (5) The criteria for determining how a research project or economic development
31 opportunity is recommended to the Governor for an award from the fund;
32 (6) Any requirements that the individual or entity applying for an award must meet in
33 order to receive the award;
